def: A Venetian coin, worth about three English farthings, or oneand a half cents. [Obs.]
The act of experimenting; practice by experiment. J. S. Mill.
Of or pertaining to Moravia, or to the United Brethren. SeeMoravian, n.
An internal muscle arising from the lumbar vertebr√¶ andinserted into the femur. In man there are usually two on each side,and the larger one, or great psoas, forms a part of the iliopsoas.
A genus of marine gastropods in which the shell has the outerlip dilated into a broad wing. It includes many large and handsomespecies commonly called conch shells, or conchs. See Conch.
Of or pertaining to separatism in religion; schismatical. [R.]Dr. T. Dwight.
To make mysterious; to make a mystery of.
Consisting of chyle much diluted with water; -- said of aliquid which forms the circulating fluid of some inferior animals.
Jumping, or inducing to jump; characterized by jumps; hence,extremely nervous.
